        "title": "Text 26",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Problem 1.1</strong></p><p><strong>How Big Are Those Boxes? Finding Volume</strong></p><p>In this globalized world, people enjoy products from many different countries. The most economical way to transport goods is by water on large container ships. </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "adNM8yx-JXm9kds-",
        "title": "Large Container Ship",
        "content": {
          "type": "Image",
          "url": "faw/images/Large-Container-Ship-FAW.png",
          "filename": "faw/images/Large-Container-Ship-FAW.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "u8y4SpuGh63oKCQf",
        "title": "Text 27",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>The ships are loaded with individual shipping containers. The containers can be easily loaded and unloaded and then transferred to trucks for delivery. </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "bn3sBdWYBy4JbhBy",
        "title": "Text 1",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Initial Challenge</strong></p><p>The shipping containers themselves are also used for temporary storage or even repurposed as homes, classrooms, or restaurants in many places.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      [
        {
          "id": "S6-v5Cg3aqwbNMlq",
