      ],
      {
        "id": "m1n5h8ObyIIjXIkH",
        "title": "Text 2",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Standard shipping containers are rectangular prisms. To decide on the right container for any particular use, it is important to know the size of the things we want to store and the size of the containers available. It is important to consider what measurements would help us decide which container to use for shipping.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "Xz6IEhN_hsH9vzK7",
        "title": "Text 3",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>To answer this question, some of Ms. Lopez&#x27;s students came up with a list of ways to measure a shipping container: length, width, height, diagonals, surface area, and volume. </p><ul><li>For each question, which measurement(s) would help you decide how to use the container for shipping or storage? Explain your reasoning. </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
